  volume={1},
  number={},
  pages={1-5},
  abstract={The primary challenge faced by distant sensor networks lies in their energy sustainability, as individual device hubs grapple with limited resources and inadequate energy efficiency. This paper undertakes an examination of the information flow within the WSNs Convention stack and puts forth a modified version of the stack. In comparison to the current WSNs Convention stack, this adapted version aims to achieve reductions in energy consumption, overall communication delay, and system failures. To cater effectively to the distinctive requirements of WSNs, the proposed protocol stack incorporates a resource sharing controller, tasked with optimizing resource allocation across all stack levels. This approach seeks to curtail packet loss during communication while upholding flow control. Through the strategic alignment of each layer’s functions with the available resources, this methodology effectively mitigates energy usage concerns.},
