  abstract={The rapid advancement of Internet of Things (IoT) technology has transformed healthcare by enabling remote patient monitoring, chronic disease management, and preventive care solutions. Human Body Communication (HBC) stands out as a promising integration within this evolution, utilizing the body's electrical conductivity for seamless data transmission between wearable health devices and healthcare systems. This direct connection ensures secure, real-time monitoring without traditional connectivity constraints. Proposing a protocol design framework, this abstract aims to optimize communication between IoT and HBC technologies to enhance health monitoring services and the framework accommodates a variety of sensors crucial for comprehensive health assessment, including temperature, EEG, ECG, heart rate, pressure, blood glucose, oxygen saturation, respiratory rate, and blood pressure sensors. By integrating IoT and HBC, healthcare enters a new era characterized by improved accessibility, efficiency, and personalized care delivery. This convergence fosters proactive healthcare, empowering individuals to manage their well-being while enabling healthcare providers to deliver timely interventions for better patient outcomes.},
